Disk intensive applications such as kubernetes can run on Raspberry Pi 4, but you need to migrate from the SD card to an SSD drive. Trust me, you don&rsquo;t want to run this from your SD card. I tried&hellip;
Preparations K3S networking does not work with nftables, so switch to legacy iptables:
pi@raspberrypi:~ $ sudo iptables -F pi@raspberrypi:~ $ sudo update-alternatives --set iptables /usr/sbin/iptables-legacy pi@raspberrypi:~ $ sudo update-alternatives --set ip6tables /usr/sbin/ip6tables-legacy pi@raspberrypi:~ $ sudo reboot The currently latest release of k3s (v1.
